  "texts": [
    "This move caused ChatGPT to quickly gain global popularity, marking the first time that large AI models broke out of the confines of the \"laboratory\" and entered the daily lives of ordinary people.",
    "Notably, prior to this, OpenAI had already introduced the GPT-1, GPT-2 and GPT-3 language models [12].",
    "In essence, ChatGPT is an upgraded version of GPT-3, known as GPT-3.5, with the addition of reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF) fine-tuning mechanisms [13].",
    "This enhancement significantly improved the model's performance.",
    "ChatGPT has demonstrated outstanding performance in various NLP domains, such as chatbots and information retrieval, attracting widespread global attention and heralding a new era in large AI model research.In May 2022, Meta also released its LLM, OPT, with parameters matching those of GPT-3, reaching 175 billion [14]."
